<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>The SQL Atlas — A Structured Journey</title>
<script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Fraunces:ital,opsz,wght,SOFT@0,9..144,300..900,0..100;1,9..144,300..900,0..100&family=Figtree:wght@300;400;500;600;700&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/marked@12/marked.min.js"></script>
<style>
  :root {
    --ink: #0c1220;
    --ink-soft: #111827;
    --ink-line: #1c2540;
    --parchment: #f3e6cf;
    --parchment-dim: #d8c9ae;
    --amber: #e5a63b;
    --amber-hot: #f5c55e;
    --teal: #67c9c0;
    --rust: #d26a4d;
    --muted: #8591a8;
    --font-scale: 1;
  }

  * { -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; }

  html, body {
    background: var(--ink);
    color: var(--parchment);
    font-family: 'Figtree', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: 0.005em;
    font-size: calc(16px * var(--font-scale));
  }

  body::before {
    content: "";
    position: fixed; inset: 0;
    pointer-events: none;
    z-index: 0;
    background:
      radial-gradient(ellipse 80% 60% at 50% 0%, rgba(229,166,59,0.06), transparent 60%),
      radial-gradient(ellipse 70% 70% at 90% 100%, rgba(103,201,192,0.05), transparent 60%),
      linear-gradient(rgba(255,255,255,0.015) 1px, transparent 1px) 0 0 / 100% 32px,
      linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.015) 1px, transparent 1px) 0 0 / 32px 100%;
  }

  .serif { font-family: 'Fraunces', serif; font-variation-settings: "opsz" 144, "SOFT" 60; }
  .mono  { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; }

  .headline {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-variation-settings: "opsz" 144, "SOFT" 100;
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    line-height: 0.95;
  }

  .small-caps {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .rule {
    height: 1px;
    background: linear-gradient(to right, transparent, var(--amber) 20%, var(--amber) 80%, transparent);
    opacity: 0.6;
  }

  .chip {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 4px;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.66rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 2px 8px;
    border-radius: 999px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(229,166,59,0.35);
    color: var(--amber-hot);
    background: rgba(229,166,59,0.06);
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .chip.teal { border-color: rgba(103,201,192,0.35); color: var(--teal); background: rgba(103,201,192,0.06); }
  .chip.rust { border-color: rgba(210,106,77,0.4); color: var(--rust); background: rgba(210,106,77,0.07); }
  .chip.muted { border-color: rgba(133,145,168,0.3); color: var(--muted); background: rgba(133,145,168,0.04); }

  @keyframes rise {
    from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(14px); }
    to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
  }
  .reveal { animation: rise 620ms cubic-bezier(0.2, 0.8, 0.2, 1) both; }

  .marquee {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-variation-settings: "opsz" 144, "SOFT" 100;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-style: italic;
    color: rgba(243,230,207,0.22);
    font-size: 10vw;
    line-height: 0.9;
    white-space: nowrap;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  @keyframes scroll-x {
    from { transform: translateX(0); }
    to { transform: translateX(-50%); }
  }
  .marquee-inner {
    display: inline-block;
    padding-left: 100%;
    animation: scroll-x 50s linear infinite;
  }

  /* ============================================
     SIDEBAR  — sticky tree TOC mirror
     ============================================ */
  .side {
    position: sticky;
    top: 1.25rem;
    max-height: calc(100vh - 2.5rem);
    overflow-y: auto;
    padding-right: 6px;
  }
  .side-heading {
    color: var(--muted);
    padding: 0 10px;
    margin: 1rem 0 0.4rem;
  }
  .sidetree details { margin: 0; }
  .sidetree summary {
    list-style: none;
    cursor: pointer;
    padding: 5px 10px;
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    border-left: 2px solid transparent;
    transition: all 160ms ease;
  }
  /* hide ALL native markers — we use ::marker for a single custom arrow */
  .sidetree summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
  .sidetree summary { list-style: none; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0; }
  .sidetree summary::before {
    content: "▸";
    display: inline-block;
    width: 16px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 0.6rem;
    transition: transform 160ms ease, color 160ms ease;
  }
  .sidetree details[open] > summary::before { transform: rotate(90deg); color: var(--amber); }
  .sidetree summary:hover { color: var(--parchment); border-left-color: var(--amber); background: rgba(229,166,59,0.04); }
  .sidetree details[open] > summary { color: var(--amber-hot); }
  .sidetree details details summary { font-size: 0.68rem; padding-left: 12px; }
  .sidetree details details details summary { padding-left: 24px; font-size: 0.66rem; opacity: 0.9; }
  .sidetree a {
    display: block;
    padding: 3px 10px 3px 34px;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.66rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    opacity: 0.85;
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .sidetree a:hover { color: var(--amber); background: rgba(229,166,59,0.04); }
  .sidetree a.active { color: var(--amber); background: rgba(229,166,59,0.08); }
  .sidetree summary .side-nav-link {
    display: inline;
    padding: 0;
    color: inherit;
    background: none;
    opacity: 1;
    text-decoration: none;
    flex: 1;
    cursor: pointer;
  }
  .sidetree summary:hover .side-nav-link { color: var(--amber); }

  /* ============================================
     FACET FILTER bar
     ============================================ */
  .facets { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 6px; }
  .facet {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.66rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 3px 9px;
    border-radius: 2px;
    border: 1px solid var(--ink-line);
    color: var(--muted);
    background: transparent;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 160ms ease;
  }
  .facet:hover { color: var(--parchment); border-color: var(--amber); }
  .facet.active { background: var(--amber); color: var(--ink); border-color: var(--amber); font-weight: 700; }

  /* ============================================
     SEARCH input + ⌘K palette
     ============================================ */
  .search {
    background: rgba(12,18,32,0.6);
    border: 1px solid var(--ink-line);
    color: var(--parchment);
    padding: 9px 14px;
    border-radius: 3px;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    width: 100%;
    outline: none;
    transition: border-color 200ms ease;
  }
  .search:focus { border-color: var(--amber); box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgba(229,166,59,0.08); }
  .search::placeholder { color: var(--muted); }

  .palette-backdrop {
    position: fixed; inset: 0;
    background: rgba(6,10,20,0.8);
    backdrop-filter: blur(6px);
    z-index: 90;
    display: none;
    align-items: flex-start;
    justify-content: center;
    padding-top: 12vh;
  }
  .palette-backdrop.open { display: flex; }
  .palette {
    width: min(640px, 92vw);
    background: var(--ink-soft);
    border: 1px solid var(--amber);
    border-radius: 4px;
    box-shadow: 0 30px 80px rgba(0,0,0,0.6);
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .palette input {
    width: 100%;
    background: transparent;
    color: var(--parchment);
    border: none;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 1rem;
    padding: 16px 20px;
    outline: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ink-line);
  }
  .palette-list {
    max-height: 48vh;
    overflow-y: auto;
    padding: 6px 0;
  }
  .palette-item {
    padding: 8px 20px;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--parchment-dim);
    display: flex;
    gap: 10px;
    align-items: center;
    cursor: pointer;
  }
  .palette-item .kind {
    font-size: 0.6rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--amber);
    width: 56px;
  }
  .palette-item.active, .palette-item:hover {
    background: rgba(229,166,59,0.1);
    color: var(--amber-hot);
  }

  /* ============================================
     PROGRESS RING
     ============================================ */
  .ring { transform: rotate(-90deg); }
  .ring-bg { stroke: var(--ink-line); }
  .ring-fg { stroke: var(--amber); stroke-linecap: round; transition: stroke-dashoffset 500ms ease; }

  /* Reading progress bar */
  .readbar {
    position: fixed; top: 0; left: 0; height: 2px;
    background: linear-gradient(to right, var(--amber), var(--rust));
    z-index: 50; transition: width 120ms ease;
  }

  /* ============================================
     RESUME CARD
     ============================================ */
  .resume {
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(229,166,59,0.07), rgba(229,166,59,0.02));
    border: 1px solid rgba(229,166,59,0.3);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--amber);
    border-radius: 3px;
    padding: 14px 18px;
    display: flex; gap: 14px; align-items: center;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .resume-icon { font-size: 1.4rem; color: var(--amber); }
  .resume-body { flex: 1; }
  .resume-label { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.68rem; letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--amber); }
  .resume-target { font-family: 'Fraunces', serif; font-size: 1.05rem; color: var(--parchment); margin-top: 2px; }

  /* ============================================
     GUIDE  — renders from embedded MD into a collapsible tree
     ============================================ */
  .guide { color: var(--parchment-dim); font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.75; }
  .guide p { margin: 0.9rem 0; max-width: 70ch; }

  .guide h1, .guide h2, .guide h3, .guide h4, .guide h5 {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-variation-settings: "opsz" 144, "SOFT" 90;
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: -0.022em;
    color: var(--parchment);
    scroll-margin-top: 1.5rem;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ========= Disclosure tree =========
     Three levels: .phase-node > .section-node > .subnode */
  .phase-node, .section-node, .subnode {
    position: relative;
    margin: 0;
  }
  /* Force-hide body when closed — Chrome's ::details-content is unreliable. */
  details:not([open]) > .phase-body,
  details:not([open]) > .section-body,
  details:not([open]) > .subnode-body,
  details:not([open]) > .guide-body,
  details:not([open]) > .guide-body-inline {
    display: none !important;
  }
  .phase-node {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--ink-line);
    padding: 0.4rem 0;
  }
  .phase-node:last-child { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ink-line); }

  .phase-node > summary,
  .section-node > summary,
  .subnode > summary {
    list-style: none;
    cursor: pointer;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.6rem 1fr auto;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
    padding: 12px 0;
    transition: background 160ms ease;
  }
  .phase-node > summary::-webkit-details-marker,
  .section-node > summary::-webkit-details-marker,
  .subnode > summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }

  .phase-node > summary:hover,
  .section-node > summary:hover,
  .subnode > summary:hover { background: rgba(229,166,59,0.03); }

  .caret-tri {
    display: inline-block;
    width: 0; height: 0;
    border: 5px solid transparent;
    border-left-color: var(--muted);
    transition: transform 200ms ease;
    transform-origin: 3px 5px;
  }
  details[open] > summary .caret-tri { transform: rotate(90deg); border-left-color: var(--amber); }

  .phase-node > summary .phase-num {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-variation-settings: "opsz" 144, "SOFT" 100;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-size: 2.6rem;
    line-height: 0.85;
    color: var(--amber);
    opacity: 0.9;
    min-width: 3rem;
    text-shadow: 0 0 28px rgba(229,166,59,0.3);
  }
  .phase-node > summary .phase-title {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-size: 1.7rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--parchment);
  }
  .phase-node > summary .phase-sub {
    display: block;
    font-family: 'Figtree', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.86rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-top: 2px;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .phase-body {
    padding: 0.6rem 0 1.8rem 3.4rem;
    border-left: 1px solid rgba(229,166,59,0.16);
    margin-left: 0.8rem;
  }

  /* Preamble (doc H1) — smaller, non-numbered, teal accent instead of amber */
  .phase-node.phase-preamble > summary {
    padding-top: 1rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.6rem;
  }
  .phase-node.phase-preamble > summary .preamble-mark {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-size: 1.8rem;
    line-height: 1;
    color: var(--teal);
    opacity: 0.7;
    min-width: 1.6rem;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .phase-node.phase-preamble > summary .phase-title {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    color: var(--parchment);
    opacity: 0.92;
    letter-spacing: 0;
  }
  .phase-node.phase-preamble > summary .phase-sub {
    font-size: 0.76rem;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    font-style: normal;
    color: var(--teal);
    opacity: 0.65;
  }
  .phase-node.phase-preamble > .phase-body {
    border-left-color: rgba(103, 201, 192, 0.22);
  }

  .section-node {
    border-top: 1px dashed rgba(28, 37, 64, 0.8);
  }
  .section-node:first-child { border-top: none; }
  .section-node > summary .sec-mark {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    color: var(--teal);
    font-size: 0.86rem;
    font-style: italic;
    opacity: 0.9;
    min-width: 3rem;
  }
  .section-node > summary .sec-title {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    color: var(--parchment);
  }
  .section-node > summary .sec-sub {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-top: 1px;
  }

  .section-body {
    padding: 0.2rem 0 1rem 3rem;
    border-left: 1px solid rgba(103,201,192,0.12);
    margin-left: 0.4rem;
  }

  .subnode > summary .sub-glyph {
    color: var(--amber);
    opacity: 0.55;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    min-width: 1.6rem;
  }
  .subnode > summary .sub-title {
    font-family: 'Figtree', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 0.98rem;
    color: var(--parchment);
  }
  .subnode-body {
    padding: 0.3rem 0 0.8rem 2.2rem;
  }

  summary .meta {
    display: flex; gap: 5px; align-items: center; flex-wrap: wrap;
    justify-content: flex-end;
  }

  /* status dot */
  .status { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.9rem; margin-right: 4px; }
  .status.todo { color: var(--muted); }
  .status.att  { color: var(--amber); }
  .status.pass { color: var(--teal); }

  /* difficulty chip colour map */
  .chip.diff-Easy   { border-color: rgba(103,201,192,0.45); color: var(--teal);  background: rgba(103,201,192,0.08); }
  .chip.diff-Medium { border-color: rgba(229,166,59,0.45);  color: var(--amber-hot); background: rgba(229,166,59,0.08); }
  .chip.diff-Hard   { border-color: rgba(210,106,77,0.5);   color: var(--rust);  background: rgba(210,106,77,0.1); }

  /* Inline MD styling inside guide bodies */
  .guide-body {
    padding-top: 0.4rem;
    animation: rise 260ms ease;
  }
  .guide-body p { margin: 0.8rem 0; max-width: 72ch; }
  .guide-body strong { color: var(--parchment); font-weight: 600; }
  .guide-body em { color: var(--parchment); font-style: italic; font-family: 'Fraunces', serif; }
  .guide-body h4 { font-size: 1rem; margin: 1.2rem 0 0.4rem; color: var(--teal); font-style: italic; }
  .guide-body h5 {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    font-size: 0.74rem;
    color: var(--amber);
    margin: 1rem 0 0.3rem;
  }
  .guide-body ul, .guide-body ol { margin: 0.6rem 0 1rem; padding-left: 1.2rem; max-width: 72ch; }
  .guide-body ul { list-style: none; }
  .guide-body ul > li { position: relative; padding-left: 1rem; margin: 0.25rem 0; }
  .guide-body ul > li::before {
    content: "◆";
    position: absolute; left: 0; top: 0;
    color: var(--amber);
    font-size: 0.58rem;
    line-height: 1.85;
    opacity: 0.7;
  }
  .guide-body ol { list-style: none; counter-reset: ol; }
  .guide-body ol > li { counter-increment: ol; position: relative; padding-left: 1.7rem; margin: 0.25rem 0; }
  .guide-body ol > li::before {
    content: counter(ol);
    position: absolute; left: 0; top: 0;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.76rem;
    color: var(--amber);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .guide-body hr {
    margin: 2rem 0; border: none; height: 1px;
    background: linear-gradient(to right, transparent, var(--ink-line) 20%, var(--ink-line) 80%, transparent);
  }
  .guide-body code {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.84em;
    background: rgba(229,166,59,0.08);
    color: var(--amber-hot);
    padding: 1px 6px;
    border-radius: 2px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(229,166,59,0.12);
  }
  .guide-body pre {
    position: relative;
    background: #060a14;
    border: 1px solid var(--ink-line);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--amber);
    border-radius: 3px;
    padding: 14px 18px;
    margin: 1rem 0;
    overflow-x: auto;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--parchment);
  }
  .guide-body pre code { background: transparent; border: none; color: inherit; padding: 0; font-size: inherit; }
  .guide-body pre .kw  { color: var(--amber-hot); font-weight: 700; }
  .guide-body pre .fn  { color: var(--teal); }
  .guide-body pre .com { color: var(--muted); font-style: italic; }
  .guide-body pre .str { color: #b8e5df; }
  .guide-body pre .num { color: var(--rust); }

  /* copy button on code blocks */
  .copy-btn {
    position: absolute; top: 6px; right: 6px;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.6rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
    background: rgba(12,18,32,0.8);
    border: 1px solid var(--ink-line);
    padding: 3px 8px;
    border-radius: 2px;
    cursor: pointer;
    opacity: 0;
    transition: opacity 160ms ease, color 160ms ease;
  }
  .guide-body pre:hover .copy-btn { opacity: 1; }
  .copy-btn:hover { color: var(--amber); border-color: var(--amber); }

  .guide-body blockquote {
    margin: 1rem 0;
    padding: 0.6rem 1.1rem;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--teal);
    background: rgba(103,201,192,0.05);
    color: var(--parchment);
    font-style: italic;
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }
  .guide-body table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin: 1.1rem 0;
    font-size: 0.88rem;
  }
  .guide-body thead { background: rgba(229,166,59,0.06); }
  .guide-body th {
    text-align: left;
    padding: 9px 14px;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: var(--amber);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ink-line);
  }
  .guide-body td {
    padding: 8px 14px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(28, 37, 64, 0.6);
    color: var(--parchment-dim);
    vertical-align: top;
  }
  .guide-body tr:hover td { background: rgba(229,166,59,0.03); }

  .guide-body a.practice-pill {
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px;
    background: var(--amber);
    color: var(--ink) !important;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    padding: 4px 10px;
    border-radius: 2px;
    text-decoration: none !important;
    transition: all 180ms ease;
  }
  .guide-body a.practice-pill:hover {
    background: var(--amber-hot);
    box-shadow: 0 4px 14px -4px rgba(229,166,59,0.5);
    transform: translateY(-1px);
  }
  /* per-pill status dot */
  .guide-body a.practice-pill .pill-dot {
    width: 7px; height: 7px; border-radius: 50%; display: inline-block;
    flex: 0 0 auto;
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px rgba(12,18,32,0.35) inset;
  }
  .pill-dot.todo { background: rgba(12,18,32,0.35); }
  .pill-dot.att  { background: #e5a63b; box-shadow: 0 0 6px rgba(229,166,59,0.7); }
  .pill-dot.pass { background: #67c9c0; box-shadow: 0 0 8px rgba(103,201,192,0.8); }
  /* deep-link flash on ?jump=<slug> */
  @keyframes pillFlash {
    0%, 100% { box-shadow: 0 0 0 0 rgba(229,166,59,0); transform: none; }
    20%      { box-shadow: 0 0 0 6px rgba(229,166,59,0.4); transform: translateY(-1px); }
  }
  .guide-body a.practice-pill.pill-flash { animation: pillFlash 1.6s ease-out; }
  /* row accent — subtly tints the row of a solved problem */
  .guide-body tr[data-status="passed"] td { background: rgba(103,201,192,0.05); }
  .guide-body tr[data-status="attempted"] td { background: rgba(229,166,59,0.035); }
  .guide-body a.xref {
    color: var(--teal);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-color: rgba(103,201,192,0.35);
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }
  .guide-body a.xref:hover { color: var(--amber-hot); text-decoration-color: var(--amber); }

  /* dimmed for facet filter */
  .tree-dim > summary { opacity: 0.28; filter: grayscale(0.3); }

  /* scrollbars */
  ::-webkit-scrollbar { width: 8px; height: 8px; }
  ::-webkit-scrollbar-track { background: var(--ink); }
  ::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb { background: var(--ink-line); border-radius: 4px; }
  ::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb:hover { background: var(--amber); }

  /* print */
  @media print {
    .side, .readbar, .palette-backdrop, .marquee, .facets, .search-row, footer, .copy-btn { display: none !important; }
    details { page-break-inside: avoid; }
    details > * { display: block !important; }
  }
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    * { animation-duration: 0.001ms !important; transition-duration: 0.001ms !important; }
  }

  footer {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--ink-line);
    margin-top: 5rem;
    padding: 3rem 0 4rem;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  /* =========================================================
     RESPONSIVE — tablet ≤1024px
     ========================================================= */
  @media (max-width: 1024px) {
    .guide-body { font-size: 0.95rem; }
    .guide-body pre { font-size: 0.8rem; padding: 0.9rem; }
    .guide-body table { font-size: 0.82rem; display: block; overflow-x: auto; -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch; }
    .guide-body th, .guide-body td { padding: 7px 10px; white-space: nowrap; }
    .facets { gap: 5px; }
    .facet { padding: 5px 10px; font-size: 0.72rem; }
    .search { font-size: 0.85rem; padding: 9px 12px; }
  }

  /* =========================================================
     RESPONSIVE — phone ≤768px
     Hide the persistent sidebar, stack hero + chips, shrink
     typography, make tables horizontally scrollable, collapse
     pacing-target rows to a stacked layout.
     ========================================================= */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    /* Prevent any intrinsic min-content child (pre, table, long word) from
       expanding the layout past the viewport — all nested scrolls stay local. */
    html, body { overflow-x: hidden !important; max-width: 100vw; }
    body { font-size: 15px; }
    header { padding-top: 4rem !important; padding-bottom: 1.5rem !important; }
    header > div { max-width: 100% !important; }
    .headline { font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 11vw, 3.5rem) !important; line-height: 1 !important; word-break: break-word; }
    header p { font-size: 1rem !important; }
    header .chip { font-size: 0.62rem; padding: 4px 9px; }

    /* Collapse the 240px side column — sidebar is already md:hidden.
       min-width:0 is critical: grid/flex items default to min-content sizing,
       and a single long table/pre/word inside would push the grid wider than
       the viewport. Clamping to 100vw plus min-width:0 forces children to
       shrink into local overflow-auto scrolls instead. */
    main {
      padding-left: 1rem !important;
      padding-right: 1rem !important;
      gap: 1rem !important;
      max-width: 100vw !important;
      grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) !important;
      min-width: 0;
    }
    main > * { min-width: 0 !important; max-width: 100% !important; }
    main pre, main code { white-space: pre-wrap !important; word-break: break-word !important; }

    /* Search + facets stack */
    .search-row { flex-direction: column !important; align-items: stretch !important; }
    .facets { overflow-x: auto; flex-wrap: nowrap; -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch; padding-bottom: 4px; }
    .facets .facet { white-space: nowrap; }

    /* Pacing target card — stack each row vertically */
    .pacing-row {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr !important;
      gap: 6px !important;
      text-align: left;
    }

    .guide-body { font-size: 0.92rem; line-height: 1.65; }
    .guide-body h1 { font-size: 1.6rem; }
    .guide-body h2 { font-size: 1.3rem; }
    .guide-body h3 { font-size: 1.1rem; }
    .guide-body pre { font-size: 0.76rem; padding: 0.75rem; }
    .guide-body table { font-size: 0.8rem; }
    .guide-body th, .guide-body td { padding: 6px 8px; }
    .guide-body blockquote { font-size: 0.92rem; padding: 0.5rem 0.9rem; }

    .phase-head, .section-head, .subnode-head { padding: 10px 12px; gap: 8px; }
    .guide-body a.practice-pill { font-size: 0.62rem; padding: 4px 8px; letter-spacing: 0.1em; }

    /* Collapse the deep left-indent tree on mobile so content gets full width.
       Desktop: 3.4 + 3 + 2.2 = ~138px of dead space on a 390px screen.
       Mobile: give each level just enough (4-10px) to show the vertical rule. */
    .phase-body   { padding: 0.5rem 0 1.2rem 0.6rem !important; margin-left: 0.2rem !important; }
    .section-body { padding: 0.3rem 0 0.8rem 0.5rem !important; margin-left: 0.15rem !important; }
    .subnode-body { padding: 0.3rem 0 0.6rem 0.4rem !important; }

    /* Tree summaries — stack meta/chips below title to stop
       1-word-per-line wrapping of long phase titles on narrow screens. */
    .phase-node > summary,
    .section-node > summary,
    .subnode > summary {
      grid-template-columns: 1.2rem 1fr !important;
      gap: 8px !important;
    }
    .phase-node > summary > .meta,
    .section-node > summary > .meta,
    .subnode > summary > .meta {
      grid-column: 2;
      margin-top: 4px;
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 4px;
    }
    .phase-node > summary .phase-num { font-size: 1.9rem !important; min-width: 2rem !important; }
    .phase-node > summary .phase-title { font-size: 1.25rem !important; }
    .phase-node > summary .phase-sub { font-size: 0.78rem; }

    /* Palette — full-screen on tiny viewports */
    .palette {
      width: calc(100vw - 28px);
      max-width: 100%;
      max-height: 70vh;
      top: 14px;
    }

    /* Resume card — stack */
    .resume { flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; gap: 8px; padding: 12px 14px; }

    /* Hide decorative marquee on tiny screens (visual noise) */
    .marquee { display: none; }

    footer { margin-top: 3rem; padding: 2rem 0 3rem; }
  }

  /* =========================================================
     RESPONSIVE — tiny phone ≤420px
     ========================================================= */
  @media (max-width: 420px) {
    header { padding-top: 3rem !important; padding-bottom: 1rem !important; }
    .guide-body { font-size: 0.88rem; }
    .guide-body pre { font-size: 0.72rem; padding: 0.6rem; }
    .guide-body table { font-size: 0.74rem; }
    .guide-body th, .guide-body td { padding: 5px 7px; }
    .guide-body a.practice-pill { font-size: 0.58rem; padding: 3px 7px; }
    .phase-head, .section-head { font-size: 0.88rem; }
  }
</style>
</head>

<body class="relative z-10">

<div class="readbar" id="readbar" style="width:0%"></div>

<!-- ================= HERO ================= -->
<header class="relative overflow-hidden pt-20 pb-10 md:pb-14">
  <div class="marquee absolute left-0 right-0 top-6 pointer-events-none select-none">
    <span class="marquee-inner">CTE · WINDOW · LAG · LEAD · GROUP&nbsp;BY · HAVING · ROW_NUMBER · RANK · DENSE_RANK · SELF&nbsp;JOIN · ANTI&nbsp;JOIN · PIVOT · SESSIONIZATION · GAPS&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;ISLANDS · CTE · WINDOW · LAG · LEAD · GROUP&nbsp;BY · HAVING · ROW_NUMBER · RANK · DENSE_RANK · SELF&nbsp;JOIN · ANTI&nbsp;JOIN · PIVOT · SESSIONIZATION · GAPS&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;ISLANDS&nbsp;·&nbsp;</span>
  </div>
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 relative">
    <h1 class="headline text-6xl md:text-8xl leading-[0.9] mb-8 reveal" style="animation-delay:.15s">
      The <em style="color:var(--amber);font-style:italic;">SQL</em> Atlas
    </h1>
    <p class="serif italic text-xl md:text-2xl max-w-2xl text-[color:var(--parchment-dim)] mb-10 reveal" style="animation-delay:.25s">
      A structured SQL interview prep guide — read the theory, then solve the problem right here in the browser. No account, no setup, progress saved locally.
    </p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 reveal" style="animation-delay:.35s">
      <span class="chip" title="Phase 0 – Phase 6 plus a Quick Reference: mental model, schema, core patterns, windows, advanced patterns, data types, performance.">7 Phases</span>
      <span class="chip teal" id="chipProblems" title="Every problem runs in an in-browser SQLite sandbox with a hidden edge-case validator.">58 Problems</span>
      <span class="chip rust" title="Your query is scored against a gold query across multiple datasets — not just the visible example. A pass means your query handles ties, NULLs, and empty groups.">Hidden Edge-Case Validator</span>
      <span class="chip muted" title="⌘K opens the jump palette · ?j / ?k move between sections · / focuses the filter.">⌘K to search · ?j for next section</span>
    </div>
    <div class="rule mt-14"></div>
  </div>
</header>

<!-- ================= MAIN LAYOUT ================= -->
<main class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 pb-20 grid md:grid-cols-[240px_1fr] gap-10 relative">

  <!-- Sticky sidebar: tree TOC mirror -->
  <aside class="hidden md:block">
    <div class="side">
      <div class="small-caps side-heading">Progress</div>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 px-3">
        <svg width="52" height="52" class="ring">
          <circle cx="26" cy="26" r="22" fill="none" stroke-width="3" class="ring-bg"></circle>
          <circle cx="26" cy="26" r="22" fill="none" stroke-width="3" class="ring-fg"
            stroke-dasharray="138.2" stroke-dashoffset="138.2" id="ringFg"></circle>
        </svg>
        <div>
          <div class="mono text-lg"><span id="progPct">0</span>%</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-[color:var(--muted)]"><span id="progCount">0</span> / <span id="progTotal">58</span> solved</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-2 px-3 mt-3">
        <button id="expandAll" class="facet">Expand</button>
        <button id="collapseAll" class="facet">Collapse</button>
        <button id="resetProg" class="facet">Reset</button>
      </div>

      <div class="small-caps side-heading mt-6">Contents</div>
      <nav id="sidetree" class="sidetree" role="tree"></nav>
    </div>
  </aside>

  <!-- Content column -->
  <section>
    <!-- Search + facets -->
    <div class="search-row flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-3 mb-5 reveal items-stretch md:items-center" style="animation-delay:.4s">
      <input id="search" class="search flex-1" placeholder="› Filter tree — or press ⌘K for jump palette" />
      <button id="paletteOpen" class="facet" style="padding:9px 14px">⌘K</button>
    </div>

    <div class="facets mb-3 reveal" style="animation-delay:.45s" id="facetBar">
      <button class="facet active" data-facet="all">All</button>
      <button class="facet" data-facet="diff:Easy">Easy</button>
      <button class="facet" data-facet="diff:Medium">Medium</button>
      <button class="facet" data-facet="diff:Hard">Hard</button>
      <button class="facet" data-facet="status:todo">Not started</button>
      <button class="facet" data-facet="status:att">Attempted</button>
      <button class="facet" data-facet="status:pass">Passed</button>
    </div>

    <!-- Resume card slot -->
    <div id="resumeSlot"></div>

    <!-- THE GUIDE (tree) -->
    <article id="guide" class="guide" role="tree"></article>

    <!-- Interview pacing (kept as product surface) -->
    <section class="mt-16 reveal">
      <div class="small-caps text-[color:var(--rust)] mb-3">Interview Dossier</div>
      <h2 class="headline text-3xl md:text-4xl mb-6">Pacing Targets</h2>
      <div style="border:1px solid rgba(210,106,77,0.25); border-radius: 4px; background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(210,106,77,0.07), transparent);">
        <div class="pacing-row grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr_auto] gap-4 px-4 py-3 items-center" style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(210,106,77,0.12);">
          <span class="chip diff-Easy">Easy</span>
          <span class="serif text-lg">Read · Plan · Write · Verify</span>
          <span class="mono text-[color:var(--teal)] text-sm">≤ 10 min</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pacing-row grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr_auto] gap-4 px-4 py-3 items-center" style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(210,106,77,0.12);">
          <span class="chip diff-Medium">Medium</span>
          <span class="serif text-lg">Identify pattern · Decompose · CTE or Window · Verify</span>
          <span class="mono text-[color:var(--amber)] text-sm">≤ 20 min</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pacing-row grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr_auto] gap-4 px-4 py-3 items-center">
          <span class="chip diff-Hard">Hard</span>
          <span class="serif text-lg">Sketch approach · Handle edges · Multi-CTE or recursion</span>
          <span class="mono text-[color:var(--rust)] text-sm">≤ 30 min</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </section>
</main>

<!-- ⌘K palette -->
<div class="palette-backdrop" id="palette">
  <div class="palette" role="dialog" aria-label="Jump palette">
    <input id="paletteInput" placeholder="Type a phase, section, pattern, or problem…" autocomplete="off" />
    <div class="palette-list" id="paletteList"></div>
  </div>
</div>

<footer class="text-center">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
    <div class="rule mb-10 opacity-40"></div>
    <p class="serif italic text-xl mb-3">&ldquo;A query is a compass. The schema is the terrain.&rdquo;</p>
    <p class="small-caps text-[color:var(--muted)]">Sandbox &middot; <span id="footerProblemCount">Fifty-eight</span> problems &middot; SQLite-WASM in your browser</p>
    <p class="mono text-[0.7rem] text-[color:var(--muted)] mt-6 uppercase tracking-widest">
      🌀 Compiled &amp; Cartographed locally &middot; No telemetry &middot; No server
    </p>
  </div>
</footer>

<script>
/* =====================================================================
   HELPERS
   ===================================================================== */
const $ = (sel, root = document) => root.querySelector(sel);
const $$ = (sel, root = document) => Array.from(root.querySelectorAll(sel));

function slugify(s) {
  return (s || "").toLowerCase()
    .replace(/[^\w\s-]/g, "")
    .trim()
    .replace(/\s+/g, "-")
    .replace(/-+/g, "-");
}

function highlightSQL(code) {
  const KW = /\b(SELECT|FROM|WHERE|GROUP|BY|HAVING|ORDER|LIMIT|OFFSET|JOIN|LEFT|RIGHT|FULL|INNER|OUTER|CROSS|LATERAL|ON|AS|AND|OR|NOT|IN|EXISTS|BETWEEN|LIKE|IS|NULL|CASE|WHEN|THEN|ELSE|END|WITH|RECURSIVE|UNION|ALL|INTERSECT|EXCEPT|DISTINCT|OVER|PARTITION|ROWS|RANGE|PRECEDING|FOLLOWING|CURRENT|ROW|UNBOUNDED|INSERT|UPDATE|DELETE|SET|VALUES|INTO|CREATE|TABLE|INDEX|DROP|ALTER|TRUNCATE|BEGIN|COMMIT|ROLLBACK|TRANSACTION|IF|DECLARE|RETURN|GRANT|REVOKE|VIEW|TRIGGER|PROCEDURE|FUNCTION|CAST|COALESCE|EXTRACT|INTERVAL|DATE|TIMESTAMP|BOOLEAN|INT|INTEGER|BIGINT|VARCHAR|TEXT|DECIMAL|NUMERIC|FLOAT|DOUBLE|ASC|DESC|NULLS|FIRST|LAST|USING|FILTER|WITHIN|GROUPING)\b/gi;
  const FN = /\b(COUNT|SUM|AVG|MIN|MAX|ROW_NUMBER|RANK|DENSE_RANK|NTILE|LAG|LEAD|FIRST_VALUE|LAST_VALUE|NTH_VALUE|CUME_DIST|PERCENT_RANK|NOW|CURDATE|CURRENT_DATE|CURRENT_TIMESTAMP|DATEDIFF|DATE_ADD|DATE_SUB|TIMESTAMPDIFF|STR_TO_DATE|DATE_FORMAT|TO_CHAR|TO_DATE|SUBSTRING|SUBSTR|LENGTH|CHAR_LENGTH|CONCAT|CONCAT_WS|UPPER|LOWER|TRIM|REPLACE|REGEXP_REPLACE|REGEXP_MATCH|ROUND|FLOOR|CEIL|CEILING|ABS|MOD|POWER|GROUP_CONCAT|STRING_AGG|ARRAY_AGG|JSON_EXTRACT|JSON_ARRAY|JSON_OBJECT|JSON_VALUE|IFNULL|NULLIF|GREATEST|LEAST|ISNULL|EXP|LN|LOG|SIGN|SQRT)\b/gi;
  return code
    .replace(/&/g, "&amp;").replace(/</g, "&lt;").replace(/>/g, "&gt;")
    .replace(/--[^\n]*/g, m => `<span class="com">${m}</span>`)
    .replace(/\/\*[\s\S]*?\*\//g, m => `<span class="com">${m}</span>`)
    .replace(/'[^']*'/g, m => `<span class="str">${m}</span>`)
    .replace(/\b\d+(?:\.\d+)?\b/g, m => `<span class="num">${m}</span>`)
    .replace(FN, m => `<span class="fn">${m}</span>`)
    .replace(KW, m => `<span class="kw">${m.toUpperCase()}</span>`);
}

/* =====================================================================
   STATUS + PROGRESS (localStorage bridge with sandbox)
   Keys:
     atlas.status.<slug> = "attempted" | "passed"
     atlas.fontScale     = number (font-size multiplier)
   ===================================================================== */
function getStatus(slug) {
  return localStorage.getItem(`atlas.status.${slug}`) || "todo";
}
function setStatus(slug, v) {
  localStorage.setItem(`atlas.status.${slug}`, v);
}

/* paint the small status dot inside each ▶ Practice pill */
function paintPillStatuses(root = document) {
  root.querySelectorAll(".pill-dot[data-dot-slug]").forEach(d => {
    const slug = d.dataset.dotSlug;
    const s = getStatus(slug);
    d.className = "pill-dot " + (s === "passed" ? "pass" : s === "attempted" ? "att" : "todo");
    d.setAttribute("aria-hidden", "true");
    // tooltip on the PARENT pill instead (so screen readers read it once)
    const pill = d.closest("a.practice-pill");
    if (pill) pill.setAttribute("aria-label", `${s === "passed" ? "Solved" : s === "attempted" ? "Attempted" : "Practice"}: ${slug}`);
  });
  // also mark each practice-pill's row for CSS purposes
  root.querySelectorAll("a.practice-pill").forEach(a => {
    const tr = a.closest("tr");
    if (!tr) return;
    tr.dataset.status = getStatus(a.dataset.slug);
  });
}

/* =====================================================================
   PATTERN DETECTION — inspects section heading text + body to tag chips
   ===================================================================== */
const PATTERN_RULES = [
  [/anti[- ]?join/i,      "Anti-Join"],
  [/semi[- ]?join/i,      "Semi-Join"],
  [/self[- ]?join/i,      "Self-Join"],
  [/recursive|recursion/i,"Recursive CTE"],
  [/window|row_number|rank\b|lag|lead|partition/i, "Window"],
  [/pivot|unpivot/i,      "Pivot"],
  [/gaps?\s*(and|&)?\s*islands?/i, "Gaps & Islands"],
  [/session(iz|is)/i,     "Sessionization"],
  [/year[- ]?over[- ]?year|yoy|month[- ]?over/i, "YoY"],
  [/subquery|CTE/i,       "CTE"],
  [/group\s*by|HAVING/i,  "Group-By"],
  [/null/i,               "NULL"],
  [/cast|conversion/i,    "Casting"],
  [/DATE|time/i,          "Date"],
  [/JSON|array/i,         "JSON/Array"],
  [/index|EXPLAIN|sarg/i, "Performance"],
  [/transaction|DML|procedure|view/i, "Server-Side"],
];
function detectPatterns(text) {
  const hits = new Set();
  for (const [re, label] of PATTERN_RULES) {
    if (re.test(text)) hits.add(label);
  }
  return [...hits];
}

/* =====================================================================
   PHASE BLURBS (one-line teasers)
   ===================================================================== */
const PHASE_BLURBS = {
  "Phase 0": "Logical order, NULLs, casting, CASE — the mental model SQL runs on.",
  "Phase 1": "Types, constraints, normalization, engine quirks — know the table before the query.",
  "Phase 2": "GROUP BY, CTEs, JOINs, Anti/Semi-joins — the standard-query toolbox.",
  "Phase 3": "RANK · LAG · LEAD · Frames — turn rows into analytics.",
  "Phase 4": "Gaps & Islands, Intervals, Recursion, Pivot, YoY — the hard tier.",
  "Phase 5": "Date, String, JSON, Array — fluent across every data type.",
  "Phase 6": "Indexes, EXPLAIN, Sargability, DML, Views — production-quality SQL.",
};

function phaseBlurb(title) {
  const m = title.match(/^Phase\s+(\d+)/i);
  if (m) return PHASE_BLURBS[`Phase ${m[1]}`] || "";
  return "";
}

/* =====================================================================
   TREE RENDERER — turn flat markdown DOM into nested <details>
   ===================================================================== */
function buildTree(root) {
  // Pull all direct children into an array
  const flat = [...root.children];
  root.innerHTML = "";

  // Group: iterate, collect by level
  let phaseNode = null, phaseBody = null;
  let sectionNode = null, sectionBody = null;
  let subNode = null, subBody = null;
  const all = [];

  function openPhase(h1) {
    phaseNode = document.createElement("details");
    phaseNode.className = "phase-node";
    phaseNode.dataset.level = "1";
    const sum = document.createElement("summary");
    const title = h1.textContent.trim();
    const m = title.match(/^Phase\s+(\d+)\s*[—–-]?\s*(.*)/i);
    const isPhase = !!m;
    const num = m ? m[1] : "";
    const rest = m ? m[2] : title;
    // any H1 that is NOT "Phase N — …" gets preamble treatment
    if (!isPhase) {
      phaseNode.classList.add("phase-preamble");
      phaseNode.open = true; // preamble is always open by default
      sum.innerHTML = `
        <span class="caret-tri"></span>
        <span style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:14px;">
          <span class="preamble-mark">¶</span>
          <span>
            <span class="phase-title">${rest}</span>
            <span class="phase-sub">Doc preface · Legend · Navigation</span>
          </span>
        </span>
        <span class="meta"></span>
      `;
    } else {
      sum.innerHTML = `
        <span class="caret-tri"></span>
        <span style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:18px;">
          <span class="phase-num">${num}</span>
          <span>
            <span class="phase-title">${rest}</span>
            <span class="phase-sub">${phaseBlurb(title)}</span>
          </span>
        </span>
        <span class="meta"></span>
      `;
    }
    phaseNode.appendChild(sum);
    phaseBody = document.createElement("div");
    phaseBody.className = "phase-body";
    phaseNode.appendChild(phaseBody);
    phaseNode.id = slugify(title);
    phaseNode.dataset.title = title;
    root.appendChild(phaseNode);
    sectionNode = sectionBody = null;
    subNode = subBody = null;
    all.push(phaseNode);
  }

  function openSection(h2) {
    if (!phaseBody) {
      // orphan h2 (e.g. "How to Use This Guide"): give it a synthetic phase
      openPhase({ textContent: "Preface" });
    }
    sectionNode = document.createElement("details");
    sectionNode.className = "section-node";
    sectionNode.dataset.level = "2";
    const sum = document.createElement("summary");
    const title = h2.textContent.trim();
    const m = title.match(/^(\d+\.\d+)\s+(.*)$/);
    const mark = m ? `§${m[1]}` : "§";
    const rest = m ? m[2] : title;
    sum.innerHTML = `
      <span class="caret-tri"></span>
      <span style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:14px;">
        <span class="sec-mark">${mark}</span>
        <span>
          <span class="sec-title">${rest}</span>
          <span class="sec-sub"></span>
        </span>
      </span>
      <span class="meta"></span>
    `;
    sectionNode.appendChild(sum);
    sectionBody = document.createElement("div");
    sectionBody.className = "section-body";
    sectionNode.appendChild(sectionBody);
    sectionNode.id = slugify(title);
    sectionNode.dataset.title = title;
    phaseBody.appendChild(sectionNode);
    subNode = subBody = null;
    all.push(sectionNode);
  }

  function openSub(h3) {
    if (!sectionBody) {
      // orphan h3 → push into current phase (or synthetic section)
      if (!phaseBody) openPhase({ textContent: "Preface" });
      openSection({ textContent: "Details" });
    }
    subNode = document.createElement("details");
    subNode.className = "subnode";
    subNode.dataset.level = "3";
    const sum = document.createElement("summary");
    const title = h3.textContent.trim();
    sum.innerHTML = `
      <span class="caret-tri"></span>
      <span style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:10px;">
        <span class="sub-glyph">▸</span>
        <span class="sub-title">${title}</span>
      </span>
      <span class="meta"></span>
    `;
    subNode.appendChild(sum);
    subBody = document.createElement("div");
    subBody.className = "subnode-body guide-body";
    subNode.appendChild(subBody);
    subNode.id = slugify(title);
    subNode.dataset.title = title;
    sectionBody.appendChild(subNode);
    all.push(subNode);
  }

  function appendBody(node) {
    // route to innermost open container
    if (subBody) { subBody.appendChild(node); return; }
    if (sectionBody) {
      // wrap in a guide-body if not already
      let gb = sectionBody.lastElementChild;
      if (!gb || !gb.classList?.contains("guide-body-inline")) {
        gb = document.createElement("div");
        gb.className = "guide-body guide-body-inline";
        sectionBody.appendChild(gb);
      }
      gb.appendChild(node);
      return;
    }
    if (phaseBody) {
      let gb = phaseBody.lastElementChild;
      if (!gb || !gb.classList?.contains("guide-body-inline")) {
        gb = document.createElement("div");
        gb.className = "guide-body guide-body-inline";
        phaseBody.appendChild(gb);
      }
      gb.appendChild(node);
      return;
    }
    // preamble before any phase: attach to root itself as a lead-in
    root.appendChild(node);
  }

  for (const el of flat) {
    const tag = el.tagName;
    if (tag === "H1") openPhase(el);
    else if (tag === "H2") openSection(el);
    else if (tag === "H3") openSub(el);
    else appendBody(el);
  }
  return all;
}

/* =====================================================================
   DECORATE: links, code highlight, copy buttons, meta chips per node
   ===================================================================== */
function decorate(root) {
  // links — only in-browser practice anymore
  root.querySelectorAll("a").forEach(a => {
    const href = a.getAttribute("href") || "";
    const txt = a.textContent.trim();
    if (href.startsWith("sql_sandbox.html?slug=")) {
      const slug = href.match(/slug=([a-z0-9-]+)/)?.[1];
      a.classList.add("practice-pill");
      a.setAttribute("target", "_blank");
      a.setAttribute("rel", "noopener");
      a.dataset.slug = slug || "";
      a.innerHTML = `<span class="pill-dot" data-dot-slug="${slug}"></span>▶ Practice`;
    } else if (href.startsWith("#")) {
      a.classList.add("xref");
    }
  });
  paintPillStatuses(root);

  // code highlight
  root.querySelectorAll("pre > code").forEach(c => {
    const lang = (c.className.match(/language-(\w+)/) || [])[1];
    if (!lang || /^sql$/i.test(lang)) {
      c.innerHTML = highlightSQL(c.textContent);
    }
    // copy button
    const pre = c.parentElement;
    if (pre && !pre.querySelector(".copy-btn")) {
      const btn = document.createElement("button");
      btn.className = "copy-btn";
      btn.textContent = "Copy";
      btn.addEventListener("click", async (e) => {
        e.stopPropagation();
        await navigator.clipboard.writeText(c.textContent);
        btn.textContent = "Copied";
        setTimeout(() => btn.textContent = "Copy", 1400);
      });
      pre.appendChild(btn);
    }
  });
}

/* =====================================================================
   COMPUTE + PAINT meta chips (difficulty, pattern, count, status) on every summary
   ===================================================================== */
const NODE_INDEX = []; // { id, title, level, practiceSlugs[], patterns[], difficulty }

function computeAndPaintMeta(nodes) {
  for (const node of nodes) {
    const meta = node.querySelector(":scope > summary .meta");
    if (!meta) continue;
    const title = node.dataset.title || "";
    const level = parseInt(node.dataset.level || "0");
    const isPreamble = node.classList.contains("phase-preamble");
    const bodyText = node.textContent || "";

    // collect practice slugs underneath
    const practiceLinks = node.querySelectorAll("a.practice-pill");
    const practiceSlugs = [...practiceLinks].map(a => a.dataset.slug).filter(Boolean);
    const uniq = [...new Set(practiceSlugs)];

    // patterns — detect from title + prose, return top matches
    const patterns = detectPatterns(title + " " + bodyText.slice(0, 2000));

    // difficulty histogram — count ONLY rows that also carry a practice link,
    // and dedupe by slug so a problem listed in multiple practice tables
    // inside the same section (canonical-exemplar reuse) counts once.
    let easy = 0, med = 0, hard = 0;
    const seenSlugs = new Set();
    node.querySelectorAll("table tbody tr").forEach(tr => {
      const pill = tr.querySelector("a.practice-pill");
      if (!pill) return;
      const s = pill.dataset.slug;
      if (s && seenSlugs.has(s)) return;
      if (s) seenSlugs.add(s);
      for (const td of tr.querySelectorAll("td")) {
        const t = td.textContent.trim();
        if (t === "Easy") { easy++; break; }
        else if (t === "Medium") { med++; break; }
        else if (t === "Hard") { hard++; break; }
      }
    });
    const total = easy + med + hard;

    // sample-problem leaf: if title starts with "📝 Sample Problem"
    const isProblem = /Sample Problem/i.test(title);
    const slug = node.dataset.practiceSlug
      || (isProblem ? (node.querySelector("a.practice-pill")?.dataset.slug) : null);

    // status — for leaf problems, pull from localStorage
    let statusHtml = "";
    if (slug) {
      const s = getStatus(slug);
      const cls = s === "passed" ? "pass" : (s === "attempted" ? "att" : "todo");
      const glyph = s === "passed" ? "●" : (s === "attempted" ? "◐" : "○");
      statusHtml = `<span class="status ${cls}" title="${s}">${glyph}</span>`;
      node.dataset.practiceSlug = slug;
    }

    // per-node aggregate: "X/Y ▶"
    let solvedHtml = "";
    if (uniq.length > 0 && !slug) {
      const solved = uniq.filter(s => getStatus(s) === "passed").length;
      solvedHtml = `<span class="chip muted">${solved}/${uniq.length} ▶</span>`;
    }

    // difficulty chip logic:
    //  • leaf problem: single chip of its own difficulty
    //  • section/phase WITH a practice table: show histogram "12M · 5H"
    //  • prose-only node: no chip (narrative mentions "Hard" shouldn't leak)
    let diffHtml = "";
    let dominantDiff = "";
    if (slug && total) {
      dominantDiff = hard ? "Hard" : med ? "Medium" : "Easy";
      diffHtml = `<span class="chip diff-${dominantDiff}">${dominantDiff}</span>`;
    } else if (total >= 2) {
      const parts = [];
      if (easy) parts.push(`<span class="chip diff-Easy">${easy}E</span>`);
      if (med) parts.push(`<span class="chip diff-Medium">${med}M</span>`);
      if (hard) parts.push(`<span class="chip diff-Hard">${hard}H</span>`);
      diffHtml = parts.join("");
      dominantDiff = hard >= med && hard >= easy ? "Hard" : med >= easy ? "Medium" : "Easy";
    } else if (total === 1) {
      dominantDiff = hard ? "Hard" : med ? "Medium" : "Easy";
      diffHtml = `<span class="chip diff-${dominantDiff}">${dominantDiff}</span>`;
    }

    // pattern chips: leaf → 1, section → up to 2, phase → up to 2
    const maxPats = level === 1 ? 2 : level === 2 ? 2 : 1;
    const patChipsHtml = patterns.slice(0, maxPats)
      .map(p => `<span class="chip teal">${p}</span>`).join("");

    // preamble phases (doc intro) get no chips at all
    if (isPreamble) {
      meta.innerHTML = "";
    } else {
      meta.innerHTML = statusHtml + diffHtml + patChipsHtml + solvedHtml;
    }

    // dataset tags for filter
    node.dataset.difficulty = dominantDiff || "";
    const diffSet = [];
    if (easy) diffSet.push("Easy");
    if (med)  diffSet.push("Medium");
    if (hard) diffSet.push("Hard");
    if (slug && !diffSet.length && dominantDiff) diffSet.push(dominantDiff);
    node.dataset.difficulties = diffSet.join("|"); // ← used by facet filter
    node.dataset.patterns = patterns.join("|");
    node.dataset.status = slug ? getStatus(slug) : "";
    node.dataset.practiceCount = uniq.length;

    NODE_INDEX.push({
      id: node.id,
      title,
      level: parseInt(node.dataset.level || "0"),
      patterns,
      difficulty: dominantDiff,
      slug,
      practiceCount: uniq.length,
    });

    // also stamp section-sub blurb: problem count + est reading time
    const secSub = node.querySelector(":scope > summary .sec-sub, :scope > summary .phase-sub");
    if (secSub && node.dataset.level !== "1") {
      const wc = (bodyText.match(/\b\w+\b/g) || []).length;
      const mins = Math.max(1, Math.round(wc / 220));
      const bits = [];
      if (uniq.length) bits.push(`${uniq.length} problem${uniq.length > 1 ? "s" : ""}`);
      bits.push(`${mins}m read`);
      secSub.textContent = bits.join(" · ");
    }
  }
}

/* =====================================================================
   SIDEBAR TREE (mirror of document tree)
   ===================================================================== */
function buildSidebar() {
  const side = $("#sidetree");
  side.innerHTML = "";
  const phases = $$("#guide > .phase-node");

  function makeSummary(title, targetId) {
    const s = document.createElement("summary");
    // ::before pseudo handles the single caret arrow via CSS
    s.innerHTML = `<a class="side-nav-link" data-target="${targetId}" href="#${targetId}">${title}</a>`;
    return s;
  }

  for (const ph of phases) {
    const d = document.createElement("details");
    d.appendChild(makeSummary(ph.dataset.title, ph.id));

    const sections = $$(":scope > .phase-body > .section-node", ph);
    for (const sec of sections) {
      const d2 = document.createElement("details");
      d2.appendChild(makeSummary(sec.dataset.title, sec.id));

      const subs = $$(":scope > .section-body > .subnode", sec);
      for (const sub of subs) {
        const a = document.createElement("a");
        a.href = `#${sub.id}`;
        a.textContent = sub.dataset.title;
        a.dataset.target = sub.id;
        d2.appendChild(a);
      }
      d.appendChild(d2);
    }
    side.appendChild(d);
  }

  side.addEventListener("click", (e) => {
    const a = e.target.closest("a[data-target]");
    if (!a) return;
    e.preventDefault();
    openTo(a.dataset.target);
  });
}

function openTo(idOrSlug) {
  // Try as section id first, then fall back to resolving as a practice slug
  let el = document.getElementById(idOrSlug);
  let highlightPill = null;
  if (!el) {
    highlightPill = document.querySelector(`a.practice-pill[data-slug="${idOrSlug}"]`);
    if (highlightPill) el = highlightPill.closest("tr") || highlightPill.closest(".subnode, .section-node, .phase-node");
  }
  if (!el) return;
  // open all ancestor <details>
  let cur = el;
  while (cur) {
    if (cur.tagName === "DETAILS") cur.open = true;
    cur = cur.parentElement;
  }
  el.scrollIntoView({ behavior: "smooth", block: "start" });
  if (highlightPill) {
    highlightPill.classList.add("pill-flash");
    setTimeout(() => highlightPill.classList.remove("pill-flash"), 1800);
  }
  if (history.replaceState && el.id) history.replaceState(null, "", "#" + el.id);
}

/* =====================================================================
   FACET FILTER (dim, don't hide)
   ===================================================================== */
let activeFacet = "all";
function applyFacet(facet) {
  activeFacet = facet;
  $$(".facet").forEach(b => b.classList.toggle("active", b.dataset.facet === facet));
  const nodes = $$("#guide details");
  for (const n of nodes) {
    let keep = true;
    if (facet !== "all") {
      const [kind, val] = facet.split(":");
      if (kind === "diff") {
        // keep node if ANY problem beneath it carries that difficulty
        const diffs = (n.dataset.difficulties || "").split("|").filter(Boolean);
        keep = diffs.length ? diffs.includes(val) : false;
      }
      else if (kind === "status") {
        const s = n.dataset.status;
        if (val === "todo") keep = !s || s === "todo";
        else if (val === "att") keep = s === "attempted";
        else if (val === "pass") keep = s === "passed";
      }
    }
    n.classList.toggle("tree-dim", !keep);
  }
}

/* =====================================================================
   SEARCH (live, dim non-matching)
   ===================================================================== */
let searchTimer;
function applySearch(q) {
  q = (q || "").trim().toLowerCase();
  const nodes = $$("#guide details");
  for (const n of nodes) {
    const text = (n.dataset.title + " " + (n.dataset.patterns || "")).toLowerCase();
    const hit = !q || text.includes(q);
    n.classList.toggle("tree-dim", !hit);
    if (hit && q) n.open = true;
  }
}

/* =====================================================================
   ⌘K  PALETTE
   ===================================================================== */
function openPalette() {
  $("#palette").classList.add("open");
  $("#paletteInput").value = "";
  renderPalette("");
  setTimeout(() => $("#paletteInput").focus(), 10);
}
function closePalette() { $("#palette").classList.remove("open"); }

function renderPalette(q) {
  q = q.toLowerCase().trim();
  const list = $("#paletteList");
  const hits = NODE_INDEX
    .filter(n => !q || n.title.toLowerCase().includes(q) || (n.patterns || []).some(p => p.toLowerCase().includes(q)))
    .slice(0, 30);
  list.innerHTML = hits.map((h, i) => {
    const kind = h.level === 1 ? "Phase" : h.level === 2 ? "Section" : "Topic";
    return `<div class="palette-item ${i === 0 ? "active" : ""}" data-id="${h.id}">
      <span class="kind">${kind}</span>
      <span>${h.title}</span>
    </div>`;
  }).join("") || `<div class="palette-item"><span style="color:var(--muted)">no matches</span></div>`;
  list.querySelectorAll(".palette-item").forEach(el => {
    el.addEventListener("mouseenter", () => {
      list.querySelectorAll(".palette-item").forEach(x => x.classList.remove("active"));
      el.classList.add("active");
    });
    el.addEventListener("click", () => {
      const id = el.dataset.id;
      if (id) { closePalette(); openTo(id); }
    });
  });
}

/* =====================================================================
   RESUME card — shows last attempted node
   ===================================================================== */
function paintResume() {
  const slot = $("#resumeSlot");
  if (!slot) return;
  slot.innerHTML = "";
  const last = localStorage.getItem("atlas.lastSlug");
  if (!last) return;
  // Locate the pill that links to this slug (source of truth for resolution)
  const pill = document.querySelector(`a.practice-pill[data-slug="${last}"]`);
  if (!pill) return;
  const status = getStatus(last);
  if (status === "passed") return; // nothing to resume — already solved
  // Build a breadcrumb: Phase › Section › Subnode (or problem name from the row)
  const ph  = pill.closest(".phase-node");
  const sec = pill.closest(".section-node");
  const sub = pill.closest(".subnode");
  const row = pill.closest("tr");
  const problemName = row?.querySelectorAll("td")?.[1]?.textContent?.trim() || last;
  const crumb = [ph?.dataset.title, sec?.dataset.title, sub?.dataset.title, problemName]
    .filter(Boolean).join(" › ");
  const statusLabel = status === "attempted" ? "Resume · in progress" : "Resume where you left off";
  slot.innerHTML = `
    <div class="resume">
      <div class="resume-icon">⟲</div>
      <div class="resume-body">
        <div class="resume-label">${statusLabel}</div>
        <div class="resume-target">${crumb}</div>
      </div>
      <a href="sql_sandbox.html?slug=${last}" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
         class="facet active" style="padding:7px 14px">Jump</a>
    </div>
  `;
}

/* =====================================================================
   PROGRESS RING
   ===================================================================== */
function updateProgress() {
  // Source of truth = every practice-pill rendered in the atlas. NODE_INDEX
  // only tracks heading leaves (Sample Problem sections), so it undercounts
  // practice-table rows. Scan the live DOM for unique slugs instead.
  const pillSlugs = new Set();
  document.querySelectorAll("a.practice-pill").forEach(a => {
    if (a.dataset.slug) pillSlugs.add(a.dataset.slug);
  });
  // Fall back to NODE_INDEX-derived slugs if practice pills haven't rendered yet.
  const nodeSlugs = NODE_INDEX.filter(n => n.slug).map(n => n.slug);
  const uniq = [...new Set(pillSlugs.size ? pillSlugs : nodeSlugs)];
  const solved = uniq.filter(s => getStatus(s) === "passed").length;
  const total = uniq.length || 1;
  const pct = Math.round((solved / total) * 100);
  $("#progPct").textContent = pct;
  $("#progCount").textContent = solved;
  $("#progTotal").textContent = total;
  const ring = $("#ringFg");
  const circ = 2 * Math.PI * 22;
  ring.setAttribute("stroke-dashoffset", circ * (1 - solved / total));

  // Keep the landing-page "N Problems" chip and footer in sync with
  // the real, unique, discoverable problem count.
  const chip = document.getElementById("chipProblems");
  if (chip) chip.textContent = `${uniq.length} Problems`;
  const footer = document.getElementById("footerProblemCount");
  if (footer) footer.textContent = String(uniq.length);
}

/* =====================================================================
   READING-PROGRESS bar
   ===================================================================== */
function onScroll() {
  const h = document.documentElement.scrollHeight - window.innerHeight;
  const pct = h > 0 ? window.scrollY / h : 0;
  $("#readbar").style.width = (pct * 100) + "%";
}
window.addEventListener("scroll", onScroll, { passive: true });

/* =====================================================================
   RENDER
   ===================================================================== */
function render() {
  const mdEl = $("#guide-md");
  if (!mdEl) return;
  const md = mdEl.textContent.trim();
  marked.setOptions({ gfm: true, breaks: false, headerIds: false, mangle: false });
  const guide = $("#guide");
  guide.innerHTML = marked.parse(md);
  decorate(guide);
  const nodes = buildTree(guide);
  computeAndPaintMeta(nodes);
  buildSidebar();
  updateProgress();
  paintResume();

  // deep link handling
  const hash = location.hash.slice(1);
  const jumpParam = new URLSearchParams(location.search).get("jump");
  const target = jumpParam || hash;
  if (target) {
    requestAnimationFrame(() => openTo(target));
  }
}

/* =====================================================================
   EVENT WIRING
   ===================================================================== */
document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", () => {
  render();

  // search
  $("#search").addEventListener("input", (e) => {
    clearTimeout(searchTimer);
    const v = e.target.value;
    searchTimer = setTimeout(() => applySearch(v), 120);
  });

  // facets
  $("#facetBar").addEventListener("click", (e) => {
    const b = e.target.closest(".facet");
    if (!b) return;
    applyFacet(b.dataset.facet);
  });

  // expand / collapse
  $("#expandAll").addEventListener("click", () => $$("#guide details").forEach(d => d.open = true));
  $("#collapseAll").addEventListener("click", () => $$("#guide details").forEach(d => d.open = false));
  $("#resetProg").addEventListener("click", () => {
    if (!confirm("Clear all progress for every problem?")) return;
    Object.keys(localStorage).filter(k => k.startsWith("atlas.status.") || k === "atlas.lastSlug").forEach(k => localStorage.removeItem(k));
    $$("#guide details").forEach(d => {
      delete d.dataset.status;
    });
    const nodes = $$("#guide details");
    computeAndPaintMeta(nodes.filter(n => n.dataset.title));
    updateProgress();
    paintResume();
  });

  // ⌘K
  $("#paletteOpen").addEventListener("click", openPalette);
  $("#paletteInput").addEventListener("input", (e) => renderPalette(e.target.value));
  $("#paletteInput").addEventListener("keydown", (e) => {
    const list = $("#paletteList");
    const items = [...list.querySelectorAll(".palette-item[data-id]")];
    const idx = items.findIndex(i => i.classList.contains("active"));
    if (e.key === "ArrowDown") {
      e.preventDefault();
      if (idx < items.length - 1) { items[idx]?.classList.remove("active"); items[idx + 1]?.classList.add("active"); }
    } else if (e.key === "ArrowUp") {
      e.preventDefault();
      if (idx > 0) { items[idx]?.classList.remove("active"); items[idx - 1]?.classList.add("active"); }
    } else if (e.key === "Enter") {
      const id = items.find(i => i.classList.contains("active"))?.dataset.id;
      if (id) { closePalette(); openTo(id); }
    } else if (e.key === "Escape") closePalette();
  });
  $("#palette").addEventListener("click", (e) => {
    if (e.target.id === "palette") closePalette();
  });
  window.addEventListener("keydown", (e) => {
    if ((e.metaKey || e.ctrlKey) && e.key.toLowerCase() === "k") {
      e.preventDefault(); openPalette();
    } else if (e.key === "/" && document.activeElement === document.body) {
      e.preventDefault(); $("#search").focus();
    }
  });

  // practice click — record last slug for resume
  $("#guide").addEventListener("click", (e) => {
    const a = e.target.closest("a.practice-pill");
    if (a?.dataset.slug) {
      localStorage.setItem("atlas.lastSlug", a.dataset.slug);
      // mark attempted if not already
      if (getStatus(a.dataset.slug) === "todo") setStatus(a.dataset.slug, "attempted");
    }
  });

  // storage event — refresh when sandbox writes status in another tab
  window.addEventListener("storage", (e) => {
    if (e.key?.startsWith("atlas.status.")) {
      const nodes = $$("#guide details");
      computeAndPaintMeta(nodes.filter(n => n.dataset.title));
      paintPillStatuses(document.getElementById("guide"));
      updateProgress();
      paintResume();
    }
  });
  // also refresh on tab-visible (in case sandbox ran in the same tab via popup)
  document.addEventListener("visibilitychange", () => {
    if (document.visibilityState === "visible") {
      const nodes = $$("#guide details");
      computeAndPaintMeta(nodes.filter(n => n.dataset.title));
      paintPillStatuses(document.getElementById("guide"));
      updateProgress();
      paintResume();
    }
  });
});
</script>
<!-- ================= EMBEDDED GUIDE MARKDOWN (populated by patch_atlas.py) ================= -->
<script id="guide-md" type="text/markdown"># How to Read This Atlas

> *The fastest way to master SQL in interview-ready shape.*

**Who this is for.** You can write `SELECT … FROM … WHERE …` but Hard-tier problems still stump you. This atlas gives you the **patterns** behind those problems, the **intuition** for each, and a browser sandbox to solve them end-to-end.

### Emoji legend — used consistently throughout

| Icon | Meaning |
|---|---|
| 🧠 | **Intuition** — the one-sentence mental model. Read this first. |
| ⚙️ | **Mechanics** — how the engine actually executes it. |
| ⚠️ | **Gotcha** — silent bug, wrong answer, or portability trap. |
| 💡 | **Tip** — a practical rule of thumb or dialect note. |
| 📝 | **Sample Problem** — a worked LeetCode-style example. |
| 🔗 | **Practice** — problems in the sandbox that drill this pattern. |

### Recommended path for a first-time reader

1. **Phase 0** — mental model (logical order, NULL, types). *Skipping this breaks everything downstream.*
2. **Phase 2.1 – 2.5** — aggregation, CTEs, self-joins, anti-joins. 80% of Easy/Medium problems live here.
3. **Phase 3.1 – 3.3** — ranking, LAG/LEAD, window frames. 80% of Medium/Hard.
4. **Phase 4.1** — gaps & islands. The single most-asked "Hard" pattern.
5. **Phase 5.1 – 5.2** — dates and string aggregation. Small syntax, huge interview surface area.
6. Everything else is reach-for-when-needed. The **Pattern Selection Decision Tree** at the bottom tells you which section matches your problem you're staring at.

### How to use the sandbox

Every 🔗 Practice link opens a problem in an in-browser SQLite. Type your query, hit **Run**, and a **hidden edge-case validator** compares your output against a gold query across multiple datasets — not just the visible sample. A ✅ means your query handles ties, NULLs, empty groups, and boundary cases, not just the happy path. No account. No setup. Progress saves in your browser.

### Keyboard shortcuts

| Key | Action |
|---|---|
| `⌘K` / `Ctrl+K` | Jump palette — fuzzy-search any phase, section, or problem |
| `/` | Focus the filter box |
| `?j` | Jump to the next section |
| `?k` | Jump to the previous section |

